description.narrative: Ensure that UNICEF as an organization, in its country and regional activities and in its global engagement, is better equipped to prioritize and address gender equality and human rights as cross-cutting foundational principles that there is a focus on equity and inclusion in addressing and promoting the needs and rights of children, with a particular emphasis on adolescents, children with disabilities, and the most marginalised and that communication for development is effectively used as a cross-cutting strategy for reaching and engaging underserved children and communities., which contributes to Child Poverty / Public Finance For Children, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Operations Support To Programme Delivery, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Technical Excellence In Policy And Programmes. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Technical expertise and management support provided to all UNICEF work streams for the equitable achievement of the MDGs by 2015, realizing the rights of every child in humanitarian and development contexts
